rComments: course taken years ago. professor jansen was the best thing about the history department hands down!!! her interpretation of the development of liberalism within the soviet was both nuanced and novel and i and many other young women found her to be an inspiration. the history department should give her a larger teaching package as she can do it!!!

without a doubt professor (not teaching fellow!! shes a phd noww!!!) dinah jansen is the best lecturer that I have ever had and all of her tests are tough, but insightful and i know that all of the students did very well and owe their sucess to this amazing prof!!! i took this course 2 yrs ago but it was the best and so is she!!!

Lectures were twice a week and three hours long.  I never want to do that again though the class was interesting.  It was just really long.  Thank god the class was only 6 weeks long.  The prof had lots of interesting stuff and exercises, but the length of the classes made it really tough to stay focused.  Prof was nice an helpful tho

She assigned a lot of readings.  Some of it was pretty boring, but the classes made it interesting.  She did really great class exercises that were fun.  Sometimes people went on for a long time so it was hard to get a word in but the prof tried to include everyone.

She really does seems nice enough but was all over the place and disorganized and really scattered. Also she really like's the sound of her own voice so you will need to pretend that you have an emergency or else she will keep you around as she talks at you!!   Also she is at Queens but there is no option for her at Queens so I used this one.
